            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-07-16 10:31:18" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>kind of poisonous snake; associated with lurking danger</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>asp</Gloss>
                <Gloss>cobra</Gloss>
                <Gloss>viper</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The terms ἀσπίς and ἔχιδνα[a] may be used to refer to almost any kind of poisonous snake, and since at least some type of poisonous snake occurs in practically all parts of the world, there is usually little difficulty involved in finding an appropriate term. One can, however, always employ a descriptive expression, for example, ‘a snake whose bite causes death.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
