          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-07-16 10:31:18" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of {L:ἔχιδνα&lt;SDBG:ἔχιδνα:000000&gt;}[a] ‘viper,’ {D:4.53}) a dangerous and despised person</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>evil person</Gloss>
                <Gloss>viper</Gloss>
                <Gloss>snake</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>One must exercise due caution in rendering ἔχιδνα in {S:04001203400004} and {L:ὄφις&lt;SDBG:ὄφις:000001&gt;}[b] in {S:04002303300006}, since in some cultures snakes are regarded as being particularly wise and clever, and therefore an expression such as ‘brood of vipers’ could be a compliment. In some languages important distinctions are made between different types of snakes, and therefore connotations may vary considerably.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
